# Component Architecture Standards

## Active App Structure

- `apps/web` is Astro-first.
- Route pages live in `apps/web/src/pages`.
- Shared document/layout shells live in `apps/web/src/layouts`.
- Native Astro page components live in `apps/web/src/components`.
- Page data lives in `apps/web/src/data`.
- Page helpers, metadata builders, and JSON-LD builders live in `apps/web/src/lib`.
- Generic utilities live in `apps/web/src/utils`.
- Do not create duplicate helper roots such as `lib-pages`.

## Astro Components

- Prefer `.astro` for routed/static UI.
- Use semantic HTML before ARIA.
- Keep props typed with local `type Props`.
- Keep component files flat unless a repeated component genuinely needs private helpers.
- Keep inline scripts small and scoped to the component.
- Do not add React islands unless the interaction needs client state or lifecycle APIs.

## React Components

- `packages/*`: use the package pattern, including `forwardRef` and `setDisplayName` where already established.
- `apps/web`: do not use `setDisplayName`; do not add `forwardRef` for app components.
- Co-locate component-specific types; use shared type files only when multiple files consume them.
- Use `cva` + `cn()` for stable variant APIs and plain `cn()` for one-off class composition.

## Data Boundaries

- `apps/web/src/data`: editable static records only.
- `apps/web/src/lib`: page metadata, JSON-LD, normalization, and route-level helpers.
- `apps/web/src/utils`: reusable pure utilities.
- Do not put business logic in component-local `_data` folders.
- Do not reintroduce remote content services, app API services, or generated content snapshots.

## Folder Naming

- Component folders use kebab-case.
- Component files use PascalCase for React components and concise descriptive names for Astro components.
- Tests live in `__tests__` next to the unit under test.
